bio.experienceSummary:
I'm 27 years old. I am a psychologist and a babysitter. I love my profession and working as both because I can help other people and contribute to many things. I am very cheerful, sociable, funny and calm. I'm characterized for being respectful, responsible and honest. I have worked as a nanny and as a children's psychologist. I have more than 6 years of experience in childcare. 
For me, working with children is very special, they teach us great lessons and bring us life. I think the best we can do is promote a healthy construction of childhood.

I have cared for and shared with children of all ages and I feel this has allowed me to understand them a little more in this important stage of life.

I'd describe my personality as compassionate, imaginative, and reflective

In my spare time, I like to find new nature preserves and parks to explore. I also like using an app I have to identify bird calls.

Hi there! My name is Laura and I am available for your childcare needs! I have a broad history working with children of all ages as a teacher, music and swim instructor/former lifeguard, nanny/babysitter, and camp counselor. I also have completed some early childhood education courses (child art was my favorite!). I am patient, caring, and value good communication with parents. I would be happy to speak with you about you and your child's needs! Please drop me an email and we'll go from there! Thank you!

description.originalText: Laura was great, she arrived on time and was very professional. She instantly connected with our son and dog. We felt very comfortable with her services.

bio.experienceSummary: I have years of babysitting experience for children of all ages, especially while I was in undergrad. I'm a people person with great attention to detail. I love kids and treat them with respect and dignity - I want them to have a great time while doing what they need to do. I treat peoples' homes and pets like they are my own and am willing to do any tasks that will help the family - cleaning, help with homework, making sure kids get exercise, creative or learning activities, etc. I work a corporate tech sales job from 9-6 so I am available most weeknights and certain time frames on the weekends. I am responsible and communicative with parents.

description.displayText: Ellen was very kind and punctual. I would definitely hire Ellen again.
description.originalText: Ellen was very kind and punctual. I would definitely hire Ellen again.

bio.experienceSummary: I am interested in full day-time, date nights and/or one-time sitter needs within the Atlanta area. I was a nanny most of my high school years from (two thousand to two thousand and four) and also while I was in college from (two thousand and five to two thousand and 10). I am very punctual, responsible, and a caring person. My rate starts at $20/hr. Increased by $5/child. I look forward to hearing from you soon!!! ($10-$20/day for driving)

description.originalText: Tatyanne is amazing! She has been caring for our two children (4yrs and 4mo) full time for the past couple weeks. She is so genuine and caring and we trust her completely. My 4 year old loves her and the 4 month old immediately became so attached to her. She takes direction very well and is very responsible. Bottom line- she’s incredible!

Birth and Postpartum Doula

New born care specialist

Hello Parents,

My name is Kyrie - a 33-year-old mom with over 14 years of childcare experience. I currently work at an early childhood development school, but I'm excited to return to private care to offer more personalized, thoughtful support. I'm CPR and Health & Safety certified and well-versed in caring for children at all stages of development.

I bring a warm, nurturing, and playful presence while balancing kindness with gentle structure. I truly believe in creating a safe, loving environment where children can thrive. I love sparking curiosity through arts, reading, and exploring nature, and I'm happy to collaborate on a developmentally appropriate plan tailored to your child's unique needs.

In addition to childcare, I also offer light housekeeping and meal preparation if needed. Thank you so much for your time and consideration - I'd be honored to support your family and care for your little one!

Warmly,
Kyrie

description.originalText: Was a tad late but we managed to still make things work.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi, I'm Julia! I am currently getting my PhD at Georgia Tech. I have worked part time teaching undergraduate juniors/seniors in Microbiology for the past 3 years. I received my BS from Wake Forest University as a student athlete, and received an MS from the University of South Florida. I have cared for all ages over the summers during all of high school, occasionally throughout college, and more consistently over the past year. I also watch my newborn nephew here in atl. I enjoy doing everything from being active outside to playing games inside to working on homework with kids (I especially love all things science). In my free time I like reading, health and fitness, and being outside! I have an SUV for safe transport as needed. I'm always on time, clean, organized, and give 110% to everything I do!

I work from ~ 9-5 p.m.  on weekdays, so occasional nights or weekends would be ideal!

description.originalText: Julia was incredible! She watched our son and daughter and when we came back, the kids did not want her to leave! She was great at communication and very punctual. I will be using her again in the future.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello! My name is Katelyn and I've recently moved back to the United States after teaching the International Baccalaureate program abroad. I believe in holistic learning and am a parent & classroom educator for the Positive Discipline Association. In addition to teaching Kindergarten and elementary school, I have experience as a full-time nanny for children ages 6 months and older. 

Languages: English (native), Japanese (conversationally fluent), ASL (basic)

Pets:
I have experience caring for dogs, cats, ferrets, parrots, fish, and hermit crabs. 

Regarding Covid-19 and Illness:
If someone in your family is immune compromised or sick, I will wear an N95-level mask to protect your loved ones.

Transportation:
While I do have a driver's license, I currently commute by foot and bicycle. I would like to stay within 1-3 miles of Downtown Decatur for jobs. 

Bonus: If you need a princess for a party, I can do that too.

description.originalText: Katelyn is responsive, thoughtful, kind, arrived early to our home, and wonderful to our family.

bio.experienceSummary:
I'm a caring and experienced childcare provider with a passion for helping children learn and grow. With 8 years of experience, I've had the pleasure of caring for children of all ages, from infants to preteens. I believe in creating a positive and nurturing environment where children can thrive, and I'm committed to providing the best possible care for each child in my charge.

My approach to childcare is centered around patience, creativity, and open communication. I ensure that parents are fully informed about their child's day and that any issues are addressed promptly and effectively. I'm also very comfortable enforcing household rules and boundaries to ensure a safe and structured environment for the children in my care.

I enjoy playing a variety of games with children, both indoors and outdoors, and I'm always looking for new and exciting ways to engage their imaginations.

description.displayText: Jermelaa is the best nanny ever! She is very patient, playful and kind towards my daughter. My daughter has grown very fond of her and has learned so much while in her care. I feel safe and at ease knowing my daughter is in her care and that she is in good hands. I would definitely recommend her for any family who is looking for childcare! Very reliable and does her job well.
